## GeoLearn Japan — HTTP Security Headers
## For: Cloudflare Pages / Netlify deployment
## Framework: NIST CSF · OWASP Top 10 · CIS Controls · Zero Trust
##
## Deploy on Cloudflare Pages:
##   1. Connect GitHub repo to Cloudflare Pages
##   2. Set build output directory to "/" (static site)
##   3. Set build command to: node secure-build.js
##   4. This file is auto-processed by Cloudflare Pages
##
## IMPORTANT: Do NOT enable Rocket Loader, HTML Minification,
##   or Email Obfuscation in Cloudflare Speed settings — these
##   features modify inline script content and break SHA-256 hashes.
##
## Deploy on Netlify:
##   Rename this file to netlify.toml [[headers]] format OR
##   keep as _headers (Netlify supports both formats)
## ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

